["SMF1","Chief Executive Officer","Overall responsibility for leading the firm; ensuring the business is operated with integrity and in compliance with applicable regulatory requirements; ensuring effective risk management; primary responsibility for firm's relationship with the PRA and FCA","Leading the firm's strategic direction; accountable for all Prescribed Responsibilities not allocated to other SMF holders; primary PRA/FCA supervisory contact","All process categories — ultimate accountability","Accountability controls (SMF assurance packs); preventive controls at strategic level (risk appetite, board governance)","IC1 (integrity); IC2 (due care, skill, diligence); IC3 (regulatory cooperation); IC4 (market conduct); IC6 (Consumer Duty outcomes) / SC1 (effective control); SC2 (regulatory compliance); SC3 (delegation); SC4 (disclosure to regulator)","Quarterly board papers showing strategic challenges addressed; PRA/FCA correspondence log; evidence of escalation from senior team reviewed and acted upon; board-level risk appetite statement approved; any direction to the firm reviewed and responded to within required timeframe","CTL-SMC-001; CTL-SMC-005; CTL-SMC-006","KRI-SMCR-001 (SMF vacancy duration); KRI-SMCR-005 (SoR currency rate)","SMF1 must be UK-based and FCA/PRA pre-approved; responsible for Management Responsibilities Map accuracy; primary accountability for firm's overall compliance posture; Reasonable Steps standard under FSMA s.66A applies to all matters within scope"],
["SMF2","Chief Financial Officer","Responsibility for the firm's financial reporting, financial controls and capital adequacy; responsibility for prudential reporting to the PRA; responsibility for the ICAAP and ILAAP processes; management of the firm's liquidity position","Financial reporting and control framework; ICAAP and ILAAP preparation and submission; management of capital adequacy; ring-fencing intra-group exposure monitoring for ring-fenced banks","Finance; Capital and Liquidity; Ring-Fencing Compliance","Accountability controls (ICAAP attestation, board financial reporting sign-off); detective controls (financial controls framework)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4; IC6 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: ICAAP submission and PRA response; capital position vs. appetite; ILAAP submission; financial control framework adequacy assessment; ring-fencing intra-group exposure levels; any restatements or control weaknesses in financial reporting","CTL-OPR-005 (ring-fencing); CTL-CRD-003 (IFRS 9); CTL-SMC-006","KRI-RFB-001 (intra-group exposure); KRI-RFB-002 (prohibited activity); KRI-IFRS-001; KRI-IFRS-002","Responsible for ring-fencing compliance monitoring for ring-fenced banks above £35bn threshold (Edinburgh Reforms 2022); UK ICAAP differs from US CCAR in form and review cycle"],
["SMF3","Executive Director (additional non-CEO executive director role)","Responsibility for specified business lines or functional areas as designated in the firm's Management Responsibilities Map and Statement of Responsibilities; no standardised regulatory scope — scope set by firm's allocation","Example: accountable for the Retail Banking business line including all retail customer-facing processes and Consumer Duty obligations in the retail segment","Retail Banking (if designated); Consumer Duty outcomes in assigned business lines","Accountability controls; preventive and detective controls within assigned business lines","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4; IC6 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack for assigned business lines covering Consumer Duty outcomes MI, retail product performance, customer complaint metrics, and any conduct findings in the retail segment","CTL-COM-001; CTL-COM-002; CTL-COM-003; CTL-COM-004; CTL-COM-005","KRI-CD-001; KRI-CD-002; KRI-CD-003; KRI-CD-004","Firm-specific role — scope varies by firm; if designated as the Consumer Duty outcomes accountable executive, must demonstrate active oversight of outcomes MI"],
["SMF4","Chief Risk Officer","Responsibility for the firm's risk management framework including risk appetite, risk taxonomy, ICAAP risk sections, model risk management, and all categories of risk in the risk management framework; oversight of the three lines of defence model","Setting and maintaining risk appetite across all risk categories; oversight of the model risk management framework under SS1/23; primary accountability for operational resilience posture under PS21/3; engagement with PRA in supervisory meetings","Credit Risk; Market Risk; Operational Risk; Model Risk; Operational Resilience; Third-Party Risk","Accountability controls (risk appetite sign-off, model governance attestation, OpRes self-assessment); detective controls (KRI monitoring, risk reporting)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4; IC6 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: risk appetite vs. actual KRIs for all risk domains; ICAAP risk sections reviewed; model risk committee papers reviewed and challenged; operational resilience self-assessment adequacy; PRA supervisory meeting preparation materials; any emerging risk escalations received and actions documented","CTL-CRD-002; CTL-CRD-003; CTL-OPR-001; CTL-OPR-002; CTL-OPR-003; CTL-SMC-006","KRI-OPRES-001; KRI-OPRES-002; KRI-OPRES-003; KRI-OPRES-004; KRI-IFRS-001; KRI-IFRS-002; KRI-IFRS-003; KRI-CAP-001","PRA supervision of risk framework is the most intensive supervisory relationship for the firm; SMF4 is typically the first senior person the PRA supervisor calls with a concern; SMCR personal accountability under s.66A means SMF4 must demonstrate documented oversight of risk framework, not merely receive risk reports"],
["SMF5","Head of Internal Audit","Responsibility for the design and performance of the internal audit function; responsibility for ensuring internal audit is independent, resourced and effective; audit plan approval and oversight; reporting to the Audit Committee","Designing the risk-based internal audit plan; ensuring audit methodology meets IIA standards; reporting to Board Audit Committee; providing assurance over 1LoD and 2LoD activities; managing s.166 coordination where Internal Audit opinion is relevant","Internal Audit function — assurance over all process categories","Detective controls (audit testing, workpaper methodology); accountability controls (board Audit Committee reporting)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly report to Board Audit Committee showing: audit plan completion vs. plan; findings by severity; open issue ageing; methodology adequacy assessment; resource adequacy; any conflict of interest in audit assignments; independence assessment","CTL-AML-001 (tested); CTL-AML-002 (tested); CTL-COM-001 (tested); CTL-CRD-003 (tested)","KRI-166-001 (s.166 preparedness score)","PRA SS5/21 mandates internal audit independence; SMF5 personal accountability means the Head of Internal Audit cannot hide behind the audit plan if a material risk is not covered; s.166 findings that contradict prior IA opinions create significant SMF5 personal accountability questions"],
["SMF6","Head of Finance","Responsibility for producing accurate and timely financial information and management accounts; responsibility for the firm's tax compliance; responsibility for regulatory financial reporting (COREP, FINREP)","Producing monthly management accounts; COREP/FINREP submission to PRA; tax compliance programme; financial control framework maintenance","Finance; Financial Reporting; Regulatory Prudential Reporting","Preventive controls (financial controls); detective controls (reconciliation controls); accountability controls (board financial sign-off)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: COREP/FINREP submission timeliness; financial control testing results; any restatements or corrections to regulatory returns; material judgements in financial statements","CTL-CRD-003 (IFRS 9 linked)","KRI-IFRS-003; KRI-IFRS-004","COREP/FINREP submission quality is a PRA supervisory metric; late or incorrect submissions trigger PRA supervisory concern"],
["SMF7","Group Entity Senior Manager","Responsibility for managing the relationship between the regulated entity and its group parent; responsible for the regulated entity being managed in a way that does not compromise its ability to comply with regulatory requirements independently","Managing group-entity interface; ensuring group parent instructions do not compromise regulatory independence; overseeing management of ring-fencing independence where applicable","Group Interface; Intra-Group Transactions; Ring-Fencing Independence","Accountability controls (independence monitoring, board challenge of group instructions)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: any group parent instructions reviewed and assessed for regulatory impact; intra-group transaction pricing reviews; ring-fencing independence assessment","CTL-OPR-005 (ring-fencing)","KRI-RFB-001; KRI-RFB-002","Particularly relevant for subsidiaries of international groups where parent instructions must be assessed against UK regulatory requirements independently"],
["SMF9","Chief Operating Officer","Responsibility for operational delivery of the firm's activities including technology, operations, outsourcing, and operational resilience; primary accountability for Important Business Service delivery within impact tolerances","Technology management; Operational Resilience IBS delivery; material outsourcing oversight; day-to-day operational management; change management governance","Payments Operations; Technology; Operational Resilience; Third-Party Risk; Change Management","Preventive controls (operational controls, BCP); detective controls (incident monitoring, capacity management); accountability controls (OpRes self-assessment)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: IBS availability vs. tolerances; material outsourcer SLA performance; change management pipeline and risk assessment; incident frequency and severity trends; post-incident reviews completed","CTL-PAY-003; CTL-PAY-004; CTL-OPR-001; CTL-OPR-002; CTL-OPR-003","KRI-OPRES-001; KRI-OPRES-002; KRI-OPRES-004; KRI-APP-004","Operational Resilience PS21/3 makes operational delivery accountable at board level; COO is primary accountability for IBS availability; SMCR personal accountability means COO must demonstrate evidence of operational resilience oversight, not merely management information receipt"],
["SMF10","Chair of Risk Committee","Responsibility for chairing the Board Risk Committee effectively; ensuring the Committee provides effective challenge to the risk management framework; oversight of the relationship between Board Risk Committee and the CRO function","Chairing BRC; ensuring effective challenge of risk appetite and risk profile; overseeing escalation from the BRC to the full board; ensuring BRC has access to appropriate information","Board Risk Committee — oversight of all risk categories","Accountability controls (BRC papers and minutes evidencing substantive challenge)","IC1; IC2; IC3 / SC1; SC2; SC3","Annual review of BRC effectiveness; evidence of substantive challenge in BRC minutes; confirmation that risk appetite breaches have been escalated to full board; evidence of independent access to CRO and risk data","CTL-SMC-006 (linked)","KRI-SMCR-004 (assurance pack completeness)","FCA/PRA expect NED chairs of risk and audit committees to demonstrate substantive independent challenge; attendance alone is insufficient evidence of reasonable steps; challenge questions recorded in BRC minutes are the primary evidence"],
["SMF11","Chair of Audit Committee","Responsibility for chairing the Board Audit Committee effectively; overseeing the quality and independence of internal and external audit; oversight of the firm's internal control framework; responsibility for financial reporting integrity","Chairing BAC; overseeing internal audit independence and effectiveness; managing the external auditor relationship; reviewing and challenging ICAAP and financial control results","Board Audit Committee — oversight of internal and external audit, financial controls","Accountability controls (BAC papers and minutes evidencing challenge of audit findings and financial controls)","IC1; IC2; IC3 / SC1; SC2; SC3","Annual review of BAC effectiveness; evidence of challenge of audit findings in BAC minutes; evidence of external auditor independence assessment; review of any management letters and responses","CTL-CRD-003 (IFRS 9 — external auditor sign-off); CTL-SMC-003 (F&P — audit oversight)","KRI-166-001 (s.166 preparedness)","NED chair of Audit Committee; responsible for ensuring IA function is resourced and independent per PRA SS5/21; SMF11 personal accountability means they must evidence active oversight of audit quality, not merely attend committee meetings"],
["SMF12","Compliance Oversight (where separate from SMF16)","Where the firm has split the compliance oversight function between SMF12 and SMF16, SMF12 typically covers specific compliance areas (e.g. wholesale compliance, MAR compliance) with SMF16 covering the overall compliance framework","Compliance oversight of wholesale/capital markets activities; MAR compliance oversight; oversight of transaction reporting compliance; conflicts of interest management","Capital Markets Compliance; MAR Compliance; Wholesale Compliance","Detective controls (compliance monitoring); accountability controls (compliance attestations)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4; IC6 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering capital markets compliance monitoring results; MAR compliance findings; transaction reporting quality metrics; conflicts management process adequacy","CTL-CAP-001; CTL-CAP-002; CTL-CAP-003; CTL-CAP-004","KRI-CAP-001; KRI-CAP-002","Many mid-sized UK banks use a single SMF16 for all compliance oversight; SMF12 is more common at large investment banks and dual-regulated firms with significant wholesale activity"],
["SMF13","Head of Conduct Risk","Responsibility for overseeing conduct risk management framework; ensuring conduct risk is identified, measured and managed; oversight of the firm's conduct risk approach in relation to Consumer Duty and retail conduct","Designing and maintaining the conduct risk framework; oversight of conduct risk measurement and reporting; Consumer Duty implementation oversight (where not allocated to SMF16)","Conduct Risk; Consumer Duty Outcomes (where designated)","Detective controls (conduct risk monitoring); accountability controls (conduct risk reporting to board)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4; IC6 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering conduct risk heat map; Consumer Duty outcomes monitoring results; conduct risk appetite metrics vs. actual; thematic review of conduct findings in complaints and monitoring","CTL-COM-003; CTL-COM-004; CTL-COM-005","KRI-CD-001; KRI-CD-002; KRI-CD-003; KRI-CD-004","Consumer Duty has elevated the SMF13 profile; FCA expects conduct risk framework to be able to identify, measure and monitor whether outcomes are being delivered across all four Consumer Duty outcomes"],
["SMF16","Chief Compliance Officer / Head of Compliance","Responsibility for the design and maintenance of the firm's compliance framework; ensuring the firm complies with its regulatory obligations; overseeing the implementation of Consumer Duty; primary FCA supervisory contact for compliance matters; responsible for MLRO oversight","Compliance monitoring programme design; Consumer Duty implementation and oversight; regulatory change programme; FCA supervisory relationship management; compliance technology and GRC system governance","All compliance-critical processes — design accountability for compliance framework","Accountability controls (compliance programme attestation, Consumer Duty board report); detective controls (compliance monitoring and testing)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4; IC6 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: compliance monitoring programme results and exception rates; Consumer Duty outcomes MI summary; regulatory change pipeline assessed and actioned; open regulatory issues tracker; FCA Dear CEO letter responses; s.166 preparedness assessment score","CTL-ONB-001; CTL-ONB-002; CTL-AML-004; CTL-COM-001; CTL-COM-002; CTL-COM-003; CTL-SMC-001; CTL-SMC-002; CTL-SMC-004; CTL-SMC-005","KRI-CD-001; KRI-CD-002; KRI-CD-005; KRI-SMCR-001; KRI-SMCR-002; KRI-SMCR-003; KRI-SMCR-004; KRI-SMCR-005; KRI-166-001","SMF16 carries personal accountability under SMCR for the compliance framework design adequacy; FCA's Consumer Duty implementation review focus means SMF16 must demonstrate outcomes-based evidence, not merely process compliance; s.166 reviews of compliance frameworks directly expose SMF16 personal accountability"],
["SMF17","Chief Anti-Money Laundering Officer / MLRO","Responsibility for the firm's financial crime prevention framework as the FCA-approved Nominated Officer; direct personal accountability under POCA 2002 for DAML/SAR submission decisions; primary NCA liaison; MLRO Annual Report to board under SYSC 6.3.6R","AML/CTF programme design and oversight; sanctions compliance programme oversight; DAML consent decision-making; NCA SAR portal management; MLRO Annual Report production; financial crime training oversight","AML Transaction Monitoring; DAML Consent Management; Sanctions Screening; Financial Crime Onboarding","Accountability controls (MLRO Annual Report, DAML consent decisions); preventive controls (AML programme framework); detective controls (SAR triage)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: TM model performance metrics; SAR submission volume and timeliness; DAML consent status and register; OFSI sanctions screening SLA compliance; financial crime training completion rates; MLRO Annual Report preparation status","CTL-AML-001; CTL-AML-002; CTL-AML-003; CTL-AML-004; CTL-ONB-002; CTL-PAY-002; CTL-ONB-005","KRI-AML-001; KRI-AML-002; KRI-AML-003; KRI-AML-004; KRI-AML-005; KRI-SAR-001","SMF17 has the most distinctive UK-specific personal accountability profile of any SMF — the NCA relationship through DAML is unique; strict liability under ECTEA 2022 for OFSI sanctions breaches creates personal exposure without an intent defence; the MLRO Annual Report is a named personal document reviewed by FCA supervisors; the NatWest prosecution (2021) illustrates the institutional consequence of systemic AML failure"],
["SMF22","Other Overall Responsibility (often used for Payments / Operations / IT)","Responsibility for specified functional areas designated in the firm's Management Responsibilities Map, commonly including: Payments operations; Fraud prevention; Technology operations; Operational Resilience IBS delivery","Payments operations accountability including Faster Payments, CHAPS and cross-border SWIFT; APP fraud prevention programme ownership; CoP governance; IBS availability for Payments IBS","Payments; Fraud Prevention; Operational Resilience — Payments IBS","Preventive controls (fraud controls, CoP); detective controls (payment monitoring, fraud detection); accountability controls (payments governance)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: APP fraud reimbursement rate; CoP override rate and governance; Payments IBS availability vs. tolerance; ISO 20022 migration programme status; sanctions screening SLA; fraud operations capacity","CTL-PAY-001; CTL-PAY-002; CTL-PAY-003; CTL-PAY-004","KRI-APP-001; KRI-APP-002; KRI-APP-003; KRI-APP-004; KRI-OPRES-001","PSR PS23/3 (effective October 2024) has made APP fraud reimbursement a direct P&L event — SMF22 personal accountability for payments now includes direct financial consequence management; CoP governance is a primary PSR supervisory metric"],
["SMF24","Chief Technology Officer","Responsibility for the firm's technology strategy, architecture and operations; oversight of technology risk and cyber security programme; accountability for technology aspects of Important Business Services and Operational Resilience","Technology strategy and architecture governance; cyber security programme oversight; cloud strategy and CTP relationship management (AWS UK designated CTP from March 2025); technology change management","Technology; Cybersecurity; Cloud Infrastructure; Change Management","Preventive controls (access controls, security architecture); detective controls (security monitoring, vulnerability scanning); accountability controls (technology risk attestation)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering: cyber incident frequency and severity; vulnerability remediation rate vs. target; cloud security posture; CTP oversight assessment for AWS UK; technology change risk assessments; DR test results vs. impact tolerances","CTL-OPR-001; CTL-OPR-002; CTL-OPR-004","KRI-OPRES-001; KRI-OPRES-002; KRI-OPRES-005","FSMA 2023 Part 6A (CTP regime effective March 2025) adds a new dimension to SMF24's accountability — AWS UK as a designated CTP means SMF24 must demonstrate CTP-specific oversight that goes beyond standard third-party risk management"],
["SMF29","Head of Compliance (where used for smaller firms' single compliance SMF)","For smaller and mid-tier firms that use SMF29 as their single compliance oversight SMF covering all compliance functions including financial crime, conduct, regulatory reporting and SMCR administration","Covers all compliance functions including MLR compliance, Consumer Duty implementation, regulatory reporting, SMCR administration, and MLRO function (may be held alongside SMF17)","All compliance-critical processes","Accountability controls (entire compliance framework); detective controls (compliance monitoring)","IC1; IC2; IC3; IC4; IC6 / SC1; SC2; SC3; SC4","Quarterly assurance pack covering all compliance domains; annual MLRO report (if also SMF17); annual Consumer Duty board report","CTL-ONB-001; CTL-ONB-002; CTL-AML-001; CTL-AML-004; CTL-COM-001; CTL-COM-003; CTL-SMC-001","All KRI-CD; KRI-AML; KRI-SMCR KRIs","Used at smaller dual-regulated firms and some solo-regulated firms; dual designation as SMF16/SMF29 + SMF17 is common at mid-sized banks — creates broad personal accountability scope that may strain individual capacity"],
